<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-88-0089 </DOCNO><TEXT>In the meantime a wealth of court decisions have been reached regardingan immediate enforcement for nuclear power plants. For all that, it isstill not clear - and varying decisions have been made by the courts- according to which criteria the judicial balance is to be made betweenthe interests of the plaintiff in bringing about a stay of the proceedingsand the interests of the planner in going ahead with them. The authoradvocates an examination of the main issue already during suspensionproceedings until the court can form a preliminary opinion on the chancesof success of the main issue. He also advocates modifications in theRules of the Administrative Courts regarding immediate enforcement asdetermined in the commission draft on the Administrative Court Procedureof 1978.</TEXT></DOC>